# Security Audit Readiness - {{ project_name }}

This directory is a local educational security review for `{{ app.name }}` in namespace `{{ app.namespace }}`.

It summarizes security questions to review before moving from generated files to a real platform workflow. It does not run scanners, contact a cluster, inspect a live image, or prove runtime compliance.

## Generated files

- `container-security.md`: container hardening and image traceability review.
- `kubernetes-manifest-audit.md`: generated Kubernetes object review.
- `rbac-audit.md`: RBAC and ServiceAccount review points.
- `pod-security-audit.md`: Pod Security recommendations.
- `network-security-audit.md`: NetworkPolicy, Ingress, and TLS review.
- `secrets-audit.md`: sensitive configuration handling notes.
- `supply-chain-security.md`: Trivy, Syft, Cosign, and CI readiness notes.
- `final-security-checklist.md`: final hardening matrix.

## Important limits

This is a readiness dossier, not a live assessment. It does not execute vulnerability scanners, admission checks, RBAC queries, or cluster inspections.

Use `k8s-forge doctor` to inspect available local tooling, and use `k8s-forge supply-chain render` separately when you want local supply-chain scripts.
